This fixture is a single-file Go module where main references a package-level
constant declared in the same file. goto-definition on the reference must
resolve to the constant declaration.

Markers embedded in the source drive the test:

  query=answer  marks the identifier occurrence to query (the reference).
  target=answer marks the identifier occurrence the definition must resolve to
                (the declaration).

The harness reads these markers to compute query and expected-target positions,
so the fixture stays self-describing without hardcoded line/column numbers in
the test.

-- go.mod --
module definitionlocal

go 1.27

-- main.go --
package main

const answer = 42 // target=answer

func main() {
	println(answer) // query=answer
}
